-- Tenarist to Invest About $90 Million in Romania, ZF Says
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-11-28T07:15:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-28/tenarist-to-invest-about-90-million-in-romania-zf-says.html
Tenaris SA (TEN) , the world’s largest
maker of seamless pipes, plans to invest about $90 million in
 Romania  next year,  Ziarul Financiar  reported, citing Gabriel
Podskubka, who heads the company’s eastern European unit.  Tenaris, which invested between $80 million and $90 million
in expanding its Romania facilities this year, plans to spend
$60 million to open a factory in the western town of Zalau to
make pipes for the oil industry, the Bucharest-based newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
